Japan’s 10-Year Government Bonds Rise as Falling Stocks Spur Safety Demand

-- B y   N a o t o   H o s o d a
-- 
2011-08-05T00:06:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-05/japan-s-10-year-government-bonds-rise-as-falling-stocks-spur-safety-demand.html
Japan ’s 10-year bonds rose as sliding
stocks spurred demand for the relative safety of government
debt. The benchmark yield dropped four basis points to 0.985
percent as of 9:05 a.m. in  Tokyo , the lowest rate since
November.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
